<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 3:31PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Roosevelt,
southern Sheridan and north central Richland Counties through 430 PM
MDT...
At 331 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Culbertson, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Culbertson, Medicine Lake, Bainville, Froid, Mccabe and Homestead.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
